column5: Will be fishing Red Lake, Ontario the first week of July. Staying at a guy's cabin (doesn't fish) in St Paul Bay. Looking for fishing tips/tactics for walleye and Pike. Hazards are also important. I live and fish about 100 days/year in NE Wisconsin and am willing to share information. Dean
Howdy, Are you staying at Donny's cabin? If you need Info let me know. [email protected] And yes there's a few bad spots on the lake.... Definately will need a map... Mista W

I'm putting your request back to the top (I'm the guy from LL who told you to post here). I'm sure you'll get some more responses. Here's a link you might like:http://www.fishingmap.com/shop/lake-...nc-/page1.html Wish I could get a map for the lake I fish in Ontario.
Thanks Mista, I appreciate your assistance.
Thanks Mista, I appreciate your assistance.
